We can fetch record from db using our own custom queries like search, sorting, distinct,like patters, between dates and so on...

1. In UserRespository interface which we have created extending JpaRespository, we need to define abstract method using query like method matching method and jpa will automatically provides its implementation.

	 i. To fetch record based on lastName,
		List<User> findByLastName(String lastName);
	
	ii. To fetch record based on starting with letters : 
		List<User> findByLastNameStartingWith(String prefix);
	
	iii. To fetch record based on ending with letters : 
		List<User> findByLastNameEndingWith(String suffix);
	
	iv. To fetch record containing letters in between : 
		List<User> findByLastNameContaining(String word);
	
	v. To fetch record using AND : 
		List<User> findByFirstNameAndLastName(String fname, String lname);
	
	vi. TO fetch record using Less than any number : 
		List<User> findByAgeLessThan(int age);

	vii. TO fetch record using greater than any number including number : 
		List<User> findByAgeGreaterThanEqual(int age);

	viii. IN operator : 
		List<User> findByAgeIn(Collection<Integer> ages);

	ix. Sorting or Order By operator : 
		List<User> findByAgeOrderByFirstName(String age);


2.	find = Introducer
	By = Criteria
	Field = LastName

3. For more sql custom methods, goto https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QeRCW28jhFY&list=PL0zysOflRCelmjxj-g4jLr3WKraSU_e8q&index=14.


